com.cinchapi.concourse.util

Interface IterableByteSequences

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    FixedSizeIterableByteSequences
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CommitLog, Row

    public interface IterableByteSequences

    A class should implement this interface if it wishes to return an iterator over an array of byte sequences where the number of sequences and the size of each sequence is variable. This is usually appropriate for classes that maintain some collection(s) of non-primitive/non-fixed-size objects that are stored on disk.

    The implementing class is responsible for maintaining the byte array that holds a contiguous block of bytes representing the sequences over which to iterate. Each sequence should be preceded by a 4 byte integer that specifies how many bytes the next sequence contains. Pass the byte array into a IterableByteSequences.ByteSequencesIterator.over(byte[]), which provides built-in logic for reading sequences from a correctly formatted byte array.

    Author:
    jnelson
